lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV style=3D&quot;RIGHT: =\r\nauto&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV style=3D&quot;RIGHT: auto&quot;&gt;A deity is a cosmic energy, a=\r\nnd in the field of duality it has some attributes. Internally it is connect=\r\ned to the supreme, unspeakable, nameless entity which is impossible for the=\r\n average human mind to imagine even remotely. Some specific qualities of th=\r\nat unspeakable,&nbsp;purely transcendental&nbsp;energy are manifested in ce=\r\nrtain fashions through archetypical cosmic energies which we call deities. =\r\nThe forms/iconographies that we attribute to the&nbsp;deities are symbolic =\r\nof these qualities. For example, we can&#39;t see magnetic lines of force, but =\r\nif you keep iron-fillings, they can create a pattern and give the impressio=\r\nn of a shape.&nbsp;When perception is very subtle, due to purity of the int=\r\nernal nadis, then the energy can manifest as a form which has been created =\r\nas a symbolic&nbsp;aggregate of its different attributes. Thus each aspect =\r\nof the iconography is a representation of some quality. The lion represents=\r\n strength,\n power, raw courage, confidence and fearlessness. Exactly the qu=\r\nalities that a sadhaka will imbibe when he/she keeps successfully&nbsp;medi=\r\ntating on the iconography of Durga. Similarly&nbsp;Chamunda is savasana, si=\r\ntting on a corpse. Die to the material world you must, if you have to&nbsp;=\r\nbecome Her vehicle.&nbsp; And when you raise&nbsp;your awareness to the sha=\r\nhasrar, then you can&nbsp;percieve these cosmic&nbsp;energies without any a=\r\nttributes any more. But untill you have the ability to reach that state of =\r\nconsciousness, it is mere theory with zero real value. &lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV style=3D=\r\n&quot;RIGHT: auto&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV style=3D&quot;RIGHT: auto&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV sty=\r\nle=3D&quot;RIGHT: auto&quot;&gt;So what the Rahasya explains is the basic fundamental ic=\r\nonograph